Finally, as far as AccuracyM is concerned, another aspect of the experiment is the following: Instead of using the previous three seasons as training set and the last season as validation set, use the first 10 match days of 2018â€“19 season as training set and the remaining 28 match days as test set. In that case, AccuracyM of the Spanish La Liga rose from 51% to 70%, as seen in Fig. 3. Therefore, it is shown that present seasonâ€™s data can boost the accuracy of the model in a very beneficial manner.

